<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Section Number="0624.03" xmlns="http://StatRev.xsd"><Catchline xml:space="preserve">“Insurer” defined.</Catchline><SectionBody><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">“Insurer” includes every person engaged as indemnitor, surety, or contractor in the business of entering into contracts of insurance or of annuity.</Text></SectionBody><History xml:space="preserve">s. 3, ch. 59-205; s. 3, ch. 76-168; s. 1, ch. 77-457; ss. 2, 3, ch. 81-318; ss. 15, 809(1st), ch. 82-243; ss. 187, 188, ch. 91-108; s. 4, ch. 91-429.</History></Section>